# Proposal: kanban-board

## Intent
Build a full kanban board application from scratch that lets users manage tasks across columns with drag-and-drop, CRUD operations on cards, and local persistence.

## Scope
### In Scope
- Project scaffolding (package.json, Vite/React setup)
- Board component with 3 default columns (To Do, In Progress, Done)
- Card component with title, description display
- CRUD operations for cards (create, read, update, delete)
- Drag-and-drop cards between columns
- localStorage persistence
- Basic tests

### Out of Scope
- Backend/server-side persistence
- User authentication
- Real-time collaboration
- Custom column creation/deletion (for now)

## Capabilities
### New Capabilities
- `board-management`: Board with columns and card display
- `card-crud`: Create, read, update, delete cards
- `card-reorder`: Drag-and-drop cards between and within columns
- `data-persistence`: Save/load board state from localStorage

## Approach
React with Vite as build tool, CSS for styling (no library), react-beautiful-dnd or @dnd-kit for drag-and-drop, localStorage for persistence, Vitest + React Testing Library for testing.

## Affected Areas
| Area | Impact | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| `src/index.js` | New | Application entry point |
| `src/App.jsx` | New | Main board component |
| `src/components/` | New | Card and column components |
| `src/hooks/` | New | Custom hooks for persistence |
| `tests/` | New | Unit tests for core functionality |

## Risks
| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|------------|------------|
| Drag-and-drop library selection may affect UX quality | Med | Document library decision and provide alternatives |
| localStorage limits may be hit with large datasets | Low | Add warning about storage limits |
| No CI may lead to regressions | High | Create manual test checklist |

## Rollback Plan
git revert since there's no deployed version.

